@cory_eth I have "tiers" of passwords. For example, the sharing-tier pw is as simple as possible to remember, &amp; IDGAF who knows it. Never needs to be changed. 
Higher tiers get longer &amp; more complex pw, and if one gets compromised I only change the tier.
Have a system for pw changes too.

